One important ordering difference is now confirmed by source: D3D9’s API `setLights` only marks dirty, and the selected-light rebuild occurs at render draw time; D3D11 mutates the global dot3 snapshot immediately in `setLights` and later every draw consumes that global snapshot. I’m grabbing the D3D9 draw wrapper lines to cite that ordering directly.
